<p>
Start with rendering a simple tree:
</p>

```
YUI().use('treeview',  function(Y) {
    
    // Create a new instance of treeview, placing it in 
    // #mytree container   
    
    var tree = new Y.TreeView({
       label : "This my tree",
       children: [
           {label: "Leaf One" },
           {label: "Leaf Two"}
       ]
    });
    
    tree.render('#mytree');
```

<p>
Call the tree's `add()` method to add some leaves
with some custom markup:
</p>

```
    tree.add([{label : "<span class='new'>New leaf 1</span>"}, {label : "<span class='new'>New Leaf 2</span>"}]);
```


<p>
Then remove the first leaf:
</p>

```
    tree.item(0).remove();
```



